{"tid":1597312,"cid":11,"subCid":0,"title":"李安 x Will Smith 雙子任務 影評評分奇差","createTime":"2019-09-27T01:36:35.000Z","updateTime":"2019-10-28T03:11:00.000Z","uid":90315,"like":3,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":34,"replies":[{"pid":"05cf76e3a0885ca3b020b30e25c1ad33d35accb2","tid":1597312,"uid":90315,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-09-27T01:36:35.000Z","msg":"Metacritic 33<br />\nRotten tomatoes 29%<br />\n<br />\nVariety -<br />\nThe bizarre combination of flesh-and-blood star Will Smith, his much-younger digital clone, director Ang Lee and Jerry Bruckheimer makes for a high-concept misfire.<br />\n<br />\nHollywood Reporter -<br />\nThe disappointing end result feels less than the sum of the talents involved, a weak script and thin high-concept plot only just held together by smart visual wizardry.<br />\n<br />\nIndiewire -<br />\nThis is certainly a step forward from &ldquo;Billy Lynn&rdquo;, and a major achievement in terms of Lee&rsquo;s ongoing campaign for the medium&rsquo;s progress. But the movie is a feature-length version of what happens when you look at any one thing for too long: The object &ndash; or in this case, Will Smith&rsquo;s face &ndash; eventually stops making sense; the sheen wears off, and the armor rings hollow.<br />\n<br />\nThe Wrap -<br />\nAng Lee blends an erratic script, listless performances and high frame-rate cinematography, and the results are terrible.<br />\n<br />\n李生是咪又掛住攪技術突破，好地地拍套戲唔得咩"},{"pid":"e94e6c4a7cacea7e0a09bd83dcaa25d222258560","tid":1597312,"uid":77788,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-09-27T01:57:03.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},{"pid":"111658eb24c130aa4511b88ff3827ebf41d2cf7f","tid":1597312,"uid":179409,"like":25,"dislike":0,"score":25,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-09-27T01:57:39.000Z","msg":"李安拍呢類西式動作片<br />\n只係諗起舊版Hulk"},{"pid":"1ced8868002cac4402c75e35d6ec8714d32409f6","tid":1597312,"uid":237459,"like":3,"dislike":3,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-09-27T02:03:23.0